<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-614-749  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 614 749.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  Nov 19 1990 v24 n47 p8(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>MCI eyes consolidation, 1,500 layoffs. (MCI Communications Corp.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Anthes, Gary H.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>MCI Communications Corp will implement a restructuring of itsoperations and layoff 6 percent of its workforce as a result ofits first quarterly loss in four years.andP;  MCI's most recent quartershowed a loss of $176 million caused largely by a $550 chargeassociated with the conversion of its network to digitaltechnology.andP;  As part of the restructuring, MCI will consolidateits seven domestic divisions into into four and will layoffapproximately 1,500 employees.andP;  MCI also announced it will form anew Network Services Division tha will provide technical supportto voice and data network operations.andP;  The firm will also create abusiness marketing unit that will include four regional marketingdivisions.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   MCI Communications Corp. (Layoffs).andO;Ticker:    MCIC.andO;Topic:     ReorganizationLayoffFinancial AnalysisCost Reduction.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>